        "title": "Using Flyway application integration with Pax Exam to test OSGi application",
        "body": "<p>When trying to use <a href=\"https://code.google.com/p/flyway/wiki/ApplicationIntegration\" rel=\"nofollow\">Flyway application integration<\/a> to test an OSGi application using <a href=\"http://team.ops4j.org/wiki/display/paxexam/Pax+Exam\" rel=\"nofollow\">Pax Exam<\/a>, I get the following error:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>myTest:myTest.myTest:PaxRunnerTestContainer{felix}(com.example.sys.test.paxtests.myTest): \njavax.sql.DataSource not found by com.googlecode.flyway.core [32]\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>When I instantiate a new Flyway<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Flyway flyway = new Flyway(); \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I am provisioning Flyway and javax.sql thusly:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>return provision(\n...\nwrappedBundle(\"http://mirrors.ibiblio.org/pub/mirrors/maven2/javax/sql/jdbc-stdext/2.0/jdbc-stdext-2.0-sources.jar\"),\nwrappedBundle(mavenBundle().groupId(\"com.googlecode.flyway\").artifactId(\"flyway-core\").version(\"1.5\")),\n...\n);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Is there a proper way to do this so that Flyway is aware of <code>javax.sql<\/code>? <\/p>\n",
